To this I answer, that the argument would hold, if the con- vention with him had been on the supposition of his not being a cri- minal. But when the treating with such a one has gone on with him as being such a one, we must suppose that the treaty included the remission of the penalty, so far as this matter is concerned: because, as we have elsewhere said, we must suppose such an interpretation, as provides against the whole act being null and void.
